# 🖥️ Phase 6 — Frontend Dashboard + Phase 7 — Deployment

> **Goal:** Build a simple dashboard and deploy your app live.
> **Time Estimate:** 2-3 hours
> **Skills Learned:** Fetch API, DOM manipulation, deployment workflow

---

# PART A: Frontend Dashboard (Phase 6)

Since you're a backend developer, we'll keep the frontend clean and simple — no React, no frameworks. Just HTML + CSS + Vanilla JS.

## What the Frontend Does

```
Page 1 (index.html):
  ✅ Input box for long URL
  ✅ Submit button → calls POST /api/shorten
  ✅ Shows the generated short URL
  ✅ Copy button

Page 2 (analytics.html):
  ✅ Input for short code
  ✅ Shows total clicks, creation date
  ✅ Simple stats display
```

---

## Create `client/index.html`

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>SnapLink — URL Shortener</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
  
  <!-- Google Font -->
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@300;400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>

  <div class="container">
    <header>
      <h1>⚡ SnapLink</h1>
      <p>Shorten URLs. Track clicks. Understand your audience.</p>
    </header>

    <!-- URL Shortener Form -->
    <div class="card" id="shorten-card">
      <h2>Shorten a URL</h2>

      <div class="input-group">
        <input
          type="url"
          id="longUrlInput"
          placeholder="Paste your long URL here (https://...)"
          required
        />
      </div>

      <div class="options-row">
        <label for="expiryInput">Expires in (days):</label>
        <input type="number" id="expiryInput" placeholder="e.g., 7" min="1" max="365" />
      </div>

      <button id="shortenBtn" onclick="shortenUrl()">
        <span id="btnText">Shorten URL →</span>
        <span id="btnLoader" style="display:none;">Shortening...</span>
      </button>

      <!-- Result section (hidden initially) -->
      <div class="result" id="resultSection" style="display:none;">
        <p class="result-label">Your short URL:</p>
        <div class="result-url-row">
          <a href="#" id="shortUrlDisplay" target="_blank"></a>
          <button class="copy-btn" onclick="copyUrl()">Copy</button>
        </div>
        <p class="view-analytics">
          <a href="analytics.html" id="analyticsLink">📊 View Analytics</a>
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Error section -->
      <div class="error" id="errorSection" style="display:none;">
        <p id="errorMessage"></p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

  <script src="app.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

