## GitHub README Tips (Very Important!)

Your README should include:
1. **Project title + description** with "Scalable Link Management Platform"
2. **Features list** (Redis caching, analytics, rate limiting, TTL indexes)
3. **Architecture diagram** (draw it on excalidraw.com → screenshot it)
4. **Tech stack** list
5. **API documentation** (all endpoints with request/response examples)
6. **Live demo link**
7. **How to run locally** (step by step)

---

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **For your resume:** Don't write "URL Shortener". Write:
> *"Scalable Link Management Platform with Redis caching, real-time analytics pipeline, and rate limiting — deployed on Render."*
> Same project. Completely different impression.

